g.text: In CloudFormation, parameters allow you to input custom values when you create or update a stack. This makes your CloudFormation templates more flexible,
reusable, and dynamic by letting users specify values like instance types, AMI IDs, bucket name, etc during stack creation.
* Parameters are nothing just a user inputs
- Parameters: Section where parameters are defined.
- InstanceTypeParameter: is the logical name of the parameter
- Type: The type of parameter, e.g, String, Number, List, etc.
- Default: Default value for the parameter if none is provided.
- AllowedValues: Optional list of allowed values to restrict the input
- !Ref: This is how yo reference the parameter in the Resources section.
